About Us
Baird & Russell Real Estate Team
 
As brokers of the Baird and Russell Team at John L. Scott, we offer service to all of Skagit County and beyond. Our team offers a strong expertise and knowledge of the local area, as well as, providing our clients with high standards of personalized service. Focusing on new construction, waterfront home and property management, along with residential sales and listings we are devoted to watching out for your best interests and those of your family. So whether you are purchasing a brand new home or selling a property on the lake, we are completely dedicated to helping you achieve you home buying or selling goals.
 
Danielle "Dani" Baird Russell
 
Education:Licensed Realtor since 2004Graduated from Sedro-Woolley High School in 2002. Went on to earn her bachelor's degree in Political Science from the University of Oregon where she was also a student-athlete. Participated in softball for the Ducks from 2002-2006.
Community Involvement:Kiwanis Club of Mount Vernon Member & Board Member Leadership Skagit Class of 2014 Mount Vernon Chamber of Commerce Member EDASC Member Mount Vernon Boys & Girls Club Community Council Member Former Club Director of Mount Vernon Boys & Girls Club Former Collegiate softball coach at Skagit Valley College and Bellevue Community College
 
Volunteer with: Kiwanis Salmon BBQ, Skagit Valley College Sports Auction, Sedro-Woolley High School fast pitch, Friendship House, Sedro-Woolley Thanksgiving Dinner
 
Personal:
Lives in Big Lake with her husband Michael, son Nash and dog Vader. Enjoys traveling, watching sports, rooting for the Oregon Ducks, softball and being active in the community.
 
Pam & Dan Baird
 
Education:Licensed Realtors since 1987 (Dan) and 1989 (Pam).Pam and Dan both graduated from Eisenhower High School in Yakima. Pam attended Washington State University and Dan went to Puget Sound University.
 
